===Pronunciation===
Ma*ce-do*ni-an'''
*{{SAMPA|/%m{s@"d@Uni@/}}
MAH-seh-DOH-nee-a

===Etymology===
[[Category:Greek derivations]]
From [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[μακεδονικός]]''' (''makedonikos'') "related to [[Macedonia]]".

===Adjective===
'''Macedonian'''

# Of or pertaining to the Macedonian people or language.

===Proper noun===
'''Macedonian''' (''plural:'' '''[[Macedonians]]''')

#An inhabitant, resident, or a person of descent from the ancient Macedonian kingdom, the [[Greek]] [[region]] of [[Macedonia]], the [[Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia]] or [[Bulgarian]] Macedonia.
#An [[Ancient Greek]] [[dialect]] that was spoken in the ancient Macedonian kingdom, a subbranch of the ancient Greek [[Doric]] [[dialect]].
#A [[Slavic]] ([[Slavonic]]) language (most likely a Bulgarian [[dialect]]) spoken in the Former Yugoslav Republic of Macedonia, southwestern [[Bulgaria]], northern parts of the province of Macedonia in Greece, southeastern [[Serbia and Montenegro]], and parts of far eastern [[Albania]].

